{
  "texts": [
    "In the same exercise, a more complicated function form is tested that includes mixed terms, i.e., y 3 = x 1 (1 + x 2) + cos(x 1) * sin(x 2).",
    "The difference between the true and the predicted function is illustrated in Fig. 6.",
    "The linear approach performs similarly for all three library bases.",
    "A low reconstruction error is obtained because the operation term cos(x 1) * sin(x 2) in y 3 is not enlisted in any of the libraries, showing an important limitation of the current approach.",
    "The target mathematical expression comprises m components, i.e., Y = y 1, ⋯, y m, and the goal is to learn the coefficients of a system of linear equations rather than one mathematical expression."
  ]
}